SIMPLE: stalking-horse
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stalking-horse
<hw>Stalk"ing-horse`</hw> <pr>(st⟦add⟧k"⟦icr⟧ng-h⟦ocir⟧rs`)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A horse, or a figure resembling a horse,
behind which a hunter conceals himself from the game he is aiming to
kill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>Fig.:</mark> <def>Something used to cover up a
secret project; a mask; a pretense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hypocrisy is the devil's <qex>stalking-horse</qex> under an
affectation of simplicity and religion.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How much more abominable is it to make of him [Christ] and
religion a <qex>stalking-horse</qex>, to get and enjoy the world!</q>
<rj><qau>Bunyan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stalkless</ent>⟦br⟧
